==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*skađwoz'', from Indo-European ''*skotwōs''.  Cognate with Old High German ''[[scato]]'' (German ''[[schatten]]''), Gothic [[𐍃𐌺𐌰𐌳𐌿𐍃]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek ''[[σκότος]]'', Celtic ''*skātos'' (Irish ''[[scáth]]'', Breton ''[[squeut]]'').

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈʃæɑdu/}}

===Noun===
'''sceadu''' {{f}} (plural '''[[sceaduwe]]''')

# [[shadow]], [[darkness]]

